#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta author="Bhikkhu Brahmali"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="en"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Saṃ­ghā­di­sesa­kaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Suspension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Kuṭikā­ra­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "6. The training rule on building huts"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.145"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.246"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.6.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.1.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1417"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalanda­ka­nivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū saññācikāyo kuṭiyo kārāpenti "
"assāmikāyo attuddesikāyo appamāṇikāyo."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks of Āḷavī were building huts by means of begging. The "
"huts were intended for themselves, did not have a sponsoring owner, and were "
"inappropriate in size."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Tāyo na niṭṭhānaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "Moreover, they were never finished,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "Te yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharanti—"
msgstr "and so the monks kept on asking and begging,"

#. I have rendered <i lang="pli">muñja</i>-reed and <i lang="pli">pabbaja</i>-reed with the single word “reed.” I am not aware that these two types of reed can be distinguished in English.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid ""
"“purisaṃ detha, puri­sattha­ka­raṃ detha, goṇaṃ detha, sakaṭaṃ detha, vāsiṃ "
"detha, parasuṃ detha, kuṭhāriṃ detha, kudālaṃ detha, nikhādanaṃ detha, "
"valliṃ detha, veḷuṃ detha, muñjaṃ detha, pabbajaṃ detha, tiṇaṃ detha, "
"mattikaṃ dethā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Give a man, give a servant, give an ox, give a cart, give an adz, give a "
"hatchet, give an ax, give a spade, give a chisel, give a creeper, give "
"bamboo, give reed, give grass, give clay.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid ""
"Manussā upaddutā yācanāya upaddutā viññattiyā bhikkhū disvā ubbijjantipi "
"uttasantipi palāyantipi aññenapi gacchanti aññenapi mukhaṃ karonti dvārampi "
"thakenti,"
msgstr ""
"People felt oppressed by all the asking and begging, so much so that when "
"they saw a monk they became alarmed and fearful, and they ran away, took a "
"different path, turned away, and closed their doors."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "gāvimpi disvā palāyanti bhikkhūti maññamānā."
msgstr "They even ran away when they saw cows, thinking they were monks."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.247"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1418"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo rājagahe vassaṃvuṭṭho yena āḷavī tena pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Just then Venerable Mahākassapa, after spending the rainy season at "
"Rājagaha, set out for Āḷavī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "Anupubbena yena āḷavī tadavasari."
msgstr "When he eventually arrived in Āḷavī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā mahākassapo āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye."
msgstr "he stayed at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā patta­cīvara­mādāya "
"āḷaviṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"In the morning Venerable Mahākassapa robed up, took his bowl and robe, and "
"entered Āḷavī for alms."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid ""
"Manussā āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ passitvā ubbijjantipi uttasantipi "
"palāyantipi aññenapi gacchanti aññenapi mukhaṃ karonti dvārampi thakenti."
msgstr ""
"When people saw him they became fearful and alarmed, and they ran away, took "
"a different path, turned away, and closed their doors."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo āḷaviyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍa­pāta­paṭik­kanto bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr ""
"After finishing his almsround and eating his meal, Venerable Mahākassapa "
"returned and said to the monks:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid ""
"“pubbāyaṃ, āvuso, āḷavī subhikkhā ahosi sulabhapiṇḍā sukarā uñchena "
"paggahena yāpetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Āḷavī used to have plenty of food, and it wasn’t difficult to get by on "
"almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid ""
"etarahi panāyaṃ āḷavī dubbhikkhā dullabhapiṇḍā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena "
"yāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"But now Āḷavī is short of almsfood, and it’s not easy to get by on alms."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho, āvuso, hetu ko paccayo, yenāyaṃ āḷavī dubbhikkhā dullabhapiṇḍā, "
"na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetun”ti?"
msgstr "Why is that?”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.248"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahākassapassa etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks told Venerable Mahākassapa what had happened."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1419"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena āḷavī tena cārikaṃ "
"pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Around the same time, after staying at Rājagaha for as long as he liked, the "
"Master too set out for Āḷavī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena āḷavī tadavasari."
msgstr "When he eventually arrived at Āḷavī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye."
msgstr "he too stayed at the Aggāḷava shrine."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Venerable Mahākassapa approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahākassapo bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he told the Master what had happened."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1420"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā āḷavake bhikkhū paṭipucchi—"
msgstr ""
"The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned the monks of "
"Āḷavī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, saññācikāyo kuṭiyo kārāpetha assāmikāyo "
"attuddesikāyo appamāṇikāyo."
msgstr ""
"“Is it true, monks, that you are building huts through begging, huts "
"intended for yourself, without a sponsoring owner, and inappropriate in size?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "Tāyo na niṭṭhānaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "And that because they were never completed,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "Te tumhe yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharatha—"
msgstr "you kept on asking and begging"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"‘purisaṃ detha puri­sattha­ka­raṃ detha … pe … tiṇaṃ detha mattikaṃ dethā’ti."
msgstr "for all sorts of things,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid ""
"Manussā upaddutā yācanāya upaddutā viññattiyā bhikkhū disvā ubbijjantipi "
"uttasantipi palāyantipi aññenapi gacchanti aññenapi mukhaṃ karonti dvārampi "
"thakenti, gāvimpi disvā palāyanti bhikkhūti maññamānā”ti?"
msgstr "and people felt oppressed to point where they now avoid monks?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, saṃyācikāyo kuṭiyo kārāpessatha assāmikāyo "
"attuddesikāyo appamāṇikāyo."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you act like this?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "Tāyo na niṭṭhānaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "Te tumhe yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissatha—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid ""
"“purisaṃ detha puri­sattha­ka­raṃ detha … pe … tiṇaṃ detha mattikaṃ dethā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "Netaṃ moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "vigarahitvā dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "After rebuking them, he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Jataka"

#. </h5><div class="jataka"><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.146"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.1.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1421"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, dve bhātaro isayo gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ upanissāya vihariṃsu."
msgstr ""
"“At one time, monks, two sages who were brothers lived near the river Ganges."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.249"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ uttaritvā yena "
"kaniṭṭho isi tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"On one occasion the dragon king Maṇikaṇṭha emerged from the Ganges and "
"approached the younger sage."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.3"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ sattakkhattuṃ bhogehi parikkhipitvā "
"uparimuddhani mahantaṃ phaṇaṃ karitvā aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"He encircled him with seven coils and spread his large hood over his head."

#. VAR: bhayā → bhayāmhi (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, kaniṭṭho isi tassa nāgassa bhayā kiso ahosi lūkho "
"dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto."
msgstr ""
"Because of his fear of that dragon, the younger sage became thin, haggard, "
"and pale, his veins protruding all over his limbs."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.5"
msgid ""
"Addasa kho, bhikkhave, jeṭṭho isi kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ kisaṃ lūkhaṃ dubbaṇṇaṃ "
"uppaṇ­ḍup­paṇḍuka­jātaṃ dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gattaṃ."
msgstr "The older sage saw him like this"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.6"
msgid "Disvāna kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and asked him what was the matter."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.7"
msgid ""
"‘kissa tvaṃ, bho, kiso lūkho dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto "
"dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.8"
msgid ""
"‘Idha, bho, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ uttaritvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "And the younger sage told him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.9"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā maṃ sattakkhattuṃ bhogehi parikkhipitvā uparimuddhani mahantaṃ "
"phaṇaṃ karitvā aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.10"
msgid ""
"Tassāhaṃ, bho, nāgassa bhayā kiso lūkho dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto "
"dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.11"
msgid "‘Icchasi pana tvaṃ, bho, tassa nāgassa anāgamanan’ti?"
msgstr "The elder sage said, ‘Would you like that dragon not to return?’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.12"
msgid "‘Icchāmahaṃ, bho, tassa nāgassa anāgamanan’ti."
msgstr "‘I would.’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.13"
msgid "‘Api pana tvaṃ, bho, tassa nāgassa kiñci passasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Well then, did you see anything belonging to that dragon?’"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: maṇimassa → maṇissa (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.14"
msgid "‘Passāmahaṃ, bho, maṇimassa kaṇṭhe pilandhanan’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw an ornamental jewel on his neck.’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.15"
msgid "‘Tena hi tvaṃ, bho, taṃ nāgaṃ maṇiṃ yāca—"
msgstr "‘In that case ask the dragon for that jewel.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.16"
msgid "“maṇiṃ me, bho, dehi;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.17"
msgid "maṇinā me attho”’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1422"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.18"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ uttaritvā yena "
"kaniṭṭho isi tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Soon the dragon king again emerged from the Ganges, approached the younger "
"sage,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.19"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "and stood to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.20"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭhaṃ nāgarājānaṃ kaniṭṭho isi "
"etadavoca—"
msgstr "The sage said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.21"
msgid "‘maṇiṃ me, bho, dehi;"
msgstr "‘Sir, give me the jewel;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.22"
msgid "maṇinā me attho’ti."
msgstr "I want the jewel.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.23"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā—"
msgstr "And the dragon thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.24"
msgid "‘bhikkhu maṇiṃ yācati, bhikkhussa maṇinā attho’ti khippaññeva agamāsi."
msgstr "‘The monk is asking for the jewel,’ and he quickly departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1423"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.25"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ uttaritvā yena "
"kaniṭṭho isi tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Once more the dragon king emerged from the Ganges and approached the younger "
"sage."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.250"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.26"
msgid ""
"Addasa kho, bhikkhave, kaniṭṭho isi maṇikaṇṭhaṃ nāgarājānaṃ dūratova "
"āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "The sage saw him coming"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.27"
msgid "Disvāna maṇikaṇṭhaṃ nāgarājānaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.28"
msgid "‘maṇiṃ me, bho, dehi;"
msgstr "‘Sir, give me the jewel;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.29"
msgid "maṇinā me attho’ti."
msgstr "I want the jewel.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.30"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā—"
msgstr "When the dragon heard him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.31"
msgid "‘bhikkhu maṇiṃ yācati, bhikkhussa maṇinā attho’ti tatova paṭinivatti."
msgstr "he turned around right there."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1424"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.32"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ uttarati."
msgstr "Yet again the dragon king emerged from the Ganges."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.33"
msgid ""
"Addasa kho, bhikkhave, kaniṭṭho isi maṇikaṇṭhaṃ nāgarājānaṃ gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ "
"uttarantaṃ."
msgstr "The younger sage saw him emerging"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.34"
msgid "Disvāna maṇikaṇṭhaṃ nāgarājānaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.35"
msgid "‘maṇiṃ me, bho, dehi;"
msgstr "‘Sir, give me the jewel;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.36"
msgid "maṇinā me attho’ti."
msgstr "I want the jewel.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.37"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi—"
msgstr "The dragon king then spoke these verses to the sage:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.147"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1425"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.38"
msgid "‘Mamannapānaṃ vipulaṃ uḷāraṃ,"
msgstr "‘My food and drink are abundant and sublime,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.39"
msgid "Uppajjatīmassa maṇissa hetu;"
msgstr "And they appear because of this jewel."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.40"
msgid "Taṃ te na dassaṃ atiyācakosi,"
msgstr "I won’t give it to you—you ask too much,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.41"
msgid "Na cāpi te assama­mā­gamissaṃ."
msgstr "Nor will I return to your hermitage."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1426"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.42"
msgid "Susū yathā ­sak­kha­ra­dhota­pāṇī,"
msgstr "Like a boy holding a sharp sword,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.43"
msgid "Tāsesi maṃ selamāyācamāno;"
msgstr "You frighten me, asking for this stone."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.44"
msgid "Taṃ te na dassaṃ atiyācakosi,"
msgstr "I won’t give it to you—you ask too much,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.45"
msgid "Na cāpi te assama­mā­gamissan’ti."
msgstr "Nor will I return to your hermitage.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1427"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.46"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, maṇikaṇṭho nāgarājā—"
msgstr "And the dragon king Maṇikaṇṭha thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.47"
msgid "‘bhikkhu maṇiṃ yācati, bhikkhussa maṇinā attho’ti pakkāmi."
msgstr "‘The monk is asking for the jewel; he wants the jewel,’"

#. VAR: Tathā pakkantova → tadā pakkanto pakkantova (bj) | tadā pakkantova (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.48"
msgid "Tathā pakkantova ahosi, na puna paccāgañchi."
msgstr "and he departed and never returned."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.251"></a></p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.49"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, kaniṭṭho isi tassa nāgassa dassanīyassa adassanena "
"bhiyyoso mattāya kiso ahosi lūkho dubbaṇṇo, uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto "
"dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto."
msgstr ""
"Because he did not get to see that beautiful dragon, the young sage became "
"even thinner, more haggard and pale, his veins protruding even more."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.50"
msgid ""
"Addasa kho, bhikkhave, jeṭṭho isi kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ bhiyyoso mattāya kisaṃ "
"lūkhaṃ dubbaṇṇaṃ uppaṇ­ḍup­paṇḍuka­jātaṃ dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gattaṃ."
msgstr "The older sage saw him like this"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.51"
msgid "Disvāna kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and asked what was the matter."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.52"
msgid ""
"‘kissa tvaṃ, bho, bhiyyoso mattāya kiso lūkho dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto "
"dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto’ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.53"
msgid ""
"‘Tassāhaṃ, bho, nāgassa dassanīyassa adassanena bhiyyoso mattāya kiso lūkho "
"dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto’ti."
msgstr ""
"He replied, ‘It’s because I no longer get to see that beautiful dragon.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.54"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, jeṭṭho isi kaniṭṭhaṃ isiṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi—"
msgstr "The older sage then spoke to him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1428"></a> 
#. VAR: jigīse → jigiṃse (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.55"
msgid "‘Na taṃ yāce yassapiyaṃ jigīse,"
msgstr "‘One should not beg from those one wishes to be dear to;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Videsso → desso (bj) | desso ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.56"
msgid "Videsso hoti atiyācanāya;"
msgstr "One is detested for asking for too much."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.57"
msgid "Nāgo maṇiṃ yācito brāhmaṇena,"
msgstr "When the brahmin asked the dragon for his jewel,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.58"
msgid "Adassanaññeva tadajjhagamā’ti."
msgstr "It departed and was never to be seen again.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1429"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.59"
msgid ""
"Tesañhi nāma, bhikkhave, tiracchā­na­gatā­naṃ pāṇānaṃ amanāpā bhavissati "
"yācanā amanāpā viññatti."
msgstr "One will be disliked even by animals, monks, for asking and begging,"

#. VAR: Kimaṅgaṃ → kimaṅga (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.3.60"
msgid "Kimaṅgaṃ pana ­manus­sa­bhūtā­naṃ."
msgstr "let alone by human beings.”"

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Story"

#. </h5></div><div class="sutta"><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.148"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.1.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1430"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññataro bhikkhu himavantapasse viharati "
"aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"“At one time, monks, a certain monk lived in a forest grove on the slopes of "
"the Himalayas."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.2"
msgid "Tassa kho, bhikkhave, vanasaṇḍassa avidūre mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalaṃ."
msgstr "Not far from that grove was an large, low-lying marsh."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, mahā­sakuṇa­saṅgho tasmiṃ pallale divasaṃ gocaraṃ "
"caritvā sāyaṃ taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ vāsāya upagacchati."
msgstr ""
"A great flock of birds fed in the marsh during the day and entered the grove "
"to roost at night."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, so bhikkhu tassa sakuṇa­saṅghassa saddena ubbāḷho "
"yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"The monk was disturbed by the noise of the flocking birds, and so he came to "
"see me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "He bowed down to me, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.6"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and I said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.7"
msgid ""
"‘kacci, bhikkhu, khamanīyaṃ kacci yāpanīyaṃ kaccisi appa­kila­ma­thena "
"addhānaṃ āgato?"
msgstr ""
"‘I hope you’re keeping well, monk; I hope you’re comfortable. I hope you’re "
"not tired from traveling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.8"
msgid "Kuto ca tvaṃ, bhikkhu, āgacchasī’ti?"
msgstr "And where have you come from?’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.9"
msgid "‘Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā,"
msgstr "‘I’m keeping well, Venerable Sir;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.10"
msgid "yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā."
msgstr "I’m comfortable."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.252"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.11"
msgid "Appa­kila­ma­thena cāhaṃ, bhante, addhānaṃ āgato."
msgstr "And I’m not tired from traveling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.12"
msgid "Atthi, bhante, himavantapasse mahāvanasaṇḍo."
msgstr "On the slopes of the Himalayas there’s a great forest grove"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.13"
msgid "Tassa kho pana, bhante, vanasaṇḍassa avidūre mahantaṃ ninnaṃ pallalaṃ."
msgstr "and close by a large low-lying marsh."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, mahā­sakuṇa­saṅgho tasmiṃ pallale divasaṃ gocaraṃ caritvā "
"sāyaṃ taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ vāsāya upagacchati."
msgstr ""
"A large flock of birds feeds in that low-lying marsh during the day and "
"comes at night to roost in that forest grove."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.15"
msgid "Tato ahaṃ, bhagavā, āgacchāmi—"
msgstr "That’s where I’ve come from, Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.16"
msgid "tassa sakuṇa­saṅghassa saddena ubbāḷho’ti."
msgstr ""
"and I left because I was disturbed by the noise of that flock of birds.’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.17"
msgid "‘Icchasi pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, tassa sakuṇa­saṅghassa anāgamanan’ti?"
msgstr "‘Would you like that flock of birds not to return?’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.18"
msgid "‘Icchāmahaṃ, bhagavā, tassa sakuṇa­saṅghassa anāgamanan’ti."
msgstr "‘I would, Master.’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.19"
msgid ""
"‘Tena hi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, tattha gantvā taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā rattiyā "
"paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ tikkhattuṃ sad­da­manus­sā­vehi—"
msgstr ""
"‘Well then, go back to that forest grove. In the first part of the night, "
"call out three times,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.20"
msgid "suṇantu me, bhonto sakuṇā,"
msgstr "“Listen to me, good birds."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.21"
msgid "yāvatikā imasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe vāsaṃ upagatā, pattena me attho."
msgstr "From whoever roosts in this forest grove, I want a feather."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.22"
msgid "Ekekaṃ me, bhonto, pattaṃ dadantū’ti."
msgstr "Each one of you must give me a feather.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.23"
msgid "Rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ …"
msgstr "And in the second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.24"
msgid "rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ tikkhattuṃ sad­da­manus­sā­vehi—"
msgstr "and third part of the night do the same thing.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.25"
msgid "‘suṇantu me, bhonto sakuṇā,"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.26"
msgid "yāvatikā imasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe vāsaṃ upagatā, pattena me attho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.27"
msgid "Ekekaṃ me, bhonto, pattaṃ dadantū’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1431"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.28"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, so bhikkhu tattha gantvā taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā "
"rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ tikkhattuṃ sad­da­manus­sā­vesi—"
msgstr "The monk returned to that forest grove and did as instructed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.29"
msgid "‘suṇantu me, bhonto sakuṇā,"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.30"
msgid "yāvatikā imasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe vāsaṃ upagatā, pattena me attho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.31"
msgid "Ekekaṃ me, bhonto, pattaṃ dadantū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.32"
msgid "Rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.33"
msgid "rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ tikkhattuṃ sad­da­manus­sā­vesi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.34"
msgid "‘suṇantu me, bhonto sakuṇā,"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.35"
msgid "yāvatikā imasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe vāsaṃ upagatā, pattena me attho."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.36"
msgid "Ekekaṃ me, bhonto, pattaṃ dadantū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.37"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so sakuṇasaṅgho—"
msgstr "That flock of birds thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.38"
msgid "‘bhikkhu pattaṃ yācati bhikkhussa pattena attho’ti"
msgstr "‘The monk is asking for a feather; he wants a feather,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.39"
msgid "tamhā vanasaṇḍā pakkāmi."
msgstr "and they left that grove"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.40"
msgid "Tathā pakkantova ahosi na puna paccāgañchi."
msgstr "and never returned."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.41"
msgid ""
"Tesañhi nāma, bhikkhave, tiracchā­na­gatā­naṃ pāṇānaṃ amanāpā bhavissati "
"yācanā amanāpā viññatti."
msgstr "One will be disliked even by animals, monks, for asking and begging,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.4.42"
msgid "Kimaṅgaṃ pana ­manus­sa­bhūtā­naṃ."
msgstr "let alone by human beings.”"

#. </p></div><hr><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.1.5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1432"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, raṭṭhapālassa kulaputtassa pitā raṭṭhapālaṃ "
"kulaputtaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi—"
msgstr ""
"“The father of Raṭṭhapāla, monks, once spoke to his son with this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1433"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.2"
msgid "‘Apāhaṃ te na jānāmi,"
msgstr "‘All these people, Raṭṭhāpāla,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.3"
msgid "raṭṭhapāla bahū janā;"
msgstr "Who come to me and beg—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.4"
msgid "Te maṃ saṅgamma yācanti,"
msgstr "I don’t even know them."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.5"
msgid "kasmā maṃ tvaṃ na yācasī’ti."
msgstr "So why don’t you beg from me?’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1434"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.6"
msgid "‘Yācako appiyo hoti,"
msgstr "‘The beggar isn’t liked,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.7"
msgid "yācaṃ adadamappiyo;"
msgstr "Nor is he who doesn’t give when asked."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.8"
msgid "Tasmāhaṃ taṃ na yācāmi,"
msgstr "That’s why I do not beg from you;"

#. <br>
#. VAR: videssanā → viddesanā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.9"
msgid "mā me videssanā ahū’ti."
msgstr "Please don’t hate me for this.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.253"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1435"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.10"
msgid ""
"So hi nāma, bhikkhave, raṭṭhapālo kulaputto sakaṃ pitaraṃ evaṃ vakkhati."
msgstr ""
"If Raṭṭhapāla, who came from a good family, could speak like this to his own "
"father,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.5.11"
msgid "Kimaṅgaṃ pana jano janaṃ."
msgstr "how much more, then, can people do so to each other."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.149"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.1.6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1436"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.1"
msgid "Gihīnaṃ, bhikkhave, dussaṃharāni bhogāni sambhatānipi durakkhiyāni."
msgstr ""
"it’s hard, monks, for lay people to acquire and protect their possessions."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, evaṃ dussaṃharesu bhogesu sambhatesupi "
"durakkhiyesu yācanabahulā viññattibahulā viharissatha—"
msgstr "And still, foolish men, you kept on asking and begging"

#. VAR: parasuṃ → pharasuṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.3"
msgid ""
"‘purisaṃ detha, puri­sattha­ka­raṃ detha, goṇaṃ detha, sakaṭaṃ detha, vāsiṃ "
"detha, parasuṃ detha, kuṭhāriṃ detha, kudālaṃ detha, nikhādanaṃ detha, "
"valliṃ detha, veḷuṃ detha, muñjaṃ detha, pabbajaṃ detha, tiṇaṃ detha, "
"mattikaṃ dethā’ti."
msgstr "for all sorts of things."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.4"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.5"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1437"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.6"
msgid ""
"“Saññācikāya pana bhikkhunā kuṭiṃ kārayamānena assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ pamāṇikā "
"kāretabbā."
msgstr ""
"‘When a monk, by means of begging, builds a hut without a sponsoring owner "
"and intended for himself,"

#. That is, twelve <i lang="pli">sugata-vidatthis</i> long and seven <i lang="pli">sugata-vidatthis</i> wide inside. A <i lang="pli">vidatthi</i> is often translated as a hand-span. <i lang="pli">Sugata</i> is an epithet of the Buddha, but in this context it is used to designate a standard measure, “the standard hand-span.” The commentary, <ref>Sp.3.567.21</ref>, says that, “Here the <i lang="pli">sugata vidatthi</i> is equal to three <i lang="pli">vidatthis</i> of an average man,” <i lang="pli">sugatavidatthi nāma idāni majjhimassa purisassa tisso vidatthiyo</i>. This does not need to be understood as the Buddha being three times the size of an ordinary person, but just that the standard hand-span is three times the regular length. For the conversion into metric units I nevertheless follow the estimate of the <i lang="pli">sugata-vidatthi</i> in BMC, pp.565-566. For an explanation of the rendering “sponsoring owner,” see note to the following rule, <ref>MS.1.1515</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.7"
msgid ""
"Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso dvādasa vidatthiyo, sugata­vidat­thiyā; tiriyaṃ "
"sattantarā."
msgstr "it is to be no more than 3 meters long and 1.75 meters wide inside."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.8"
msgid "Bhikkhū abhinetabbā vatthudesanāya."
msgstr "He must get monks to approve a site"

#. VAR: vatthu → vatthuṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.9"
msgid "Tehi bhikkhūhi vatthu desetabbaṃ—"
msgstr "where no harm will be done"

#. VAR: anārambhaṃ → anārabbhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.10"
msgid "anārambhaṃ saparikkamanaṃ."
msgstr "and which has a space on all sides."

#. VAR: Sārambhe → sārabbhe (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.11"
msgid ""
"Sārambhe ce bhikkhu vatthusmiṃ aparikkamane saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kāreyya, "
"bhikkhū vā anabhineyya vatthudesanāya, pamāṇaṃ vā atikkāmeyya, "
"saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr ""
"If a monk, by means of begging, builds a hut on a site where harm will be "
"done and which lacks a space on all sides, or he does not get monks to "
"approve the site, or he exceeds the size limit, he commits an offense "
"entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs1.6.12"
msgid "(<em>6</em>:<strong>10</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.6.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.2.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.254"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1438"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Saññācikā nāma"
msgstr "By means of begging:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid ""
"sayaṃ yācitvā purisampi puri­sattha­ka­rampi goṇampi sakaṭampi vāsimpi "
"parasumpi kuṭhārimpi kudālampi nikhādanampi vallimpi veḷumpi muñjampi "
"pabbajampi tiṇampi mattikampi."
msgstr ""
"having himself begged for a man, a servant, an ox, a cart, an adz, a "
"hatchet, an ax, a spade, a chisel, a creeper, bamboo, reed, grass, clay."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1439"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Kuṭi nāma"
msgstr "A hut:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "ullittā vā hoti avalittā vā ullittāvalittā vā."
msgstr "a wattle and daub hut."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1440"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Kārayamānenāti"
msgstr "Builds:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "karonto vā kārāpento vā."
msgstr "building it himself or getting someone else to build it."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1441"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Assāmikanti"
msgstr "Without a sponsoring owner:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "na añño koci sāmiko hoti, itthī vā puriso vā gahaṭṭho vā pabbajito vā."
msgstr ""
"there is no other owner, either a woman or a man, either a lay person or one "
"gone forth."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1442"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Attuddesanti"
msgstr "Intended for himself:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "attano atthāya."
msgstr "for his own use."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1443"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Pamāṇikā kāretabbā."
msgstr "It is to be no more than 3 meters long:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso dvādasa vidatthiyo, sugata­vidat­thiyāti"
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "bāhirimena mānena."
msgstr "measured outside."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1444"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Tiriyaṃ sattantarāti"
msgstr "And 1.75 meters wide inside:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "abbhantarimena mānena."
msgstr "measured inside."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.150"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.2.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1445"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Bhikkhū abhinetabbā vatthudesanāyāti"
msgstr "He must get monks to approve a site:"

#. </span></p><div class="gloss"><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"tena kuṭikārakena bhikkhunā kuṭivatthuṃ sodhetvā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ "
"nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr ""
"The monk who wishes to build a hut should clear a site. He should then "
"approach the Order, put his upper robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the "
"feet of the senior monks, squat on his heels, put the palms of hands "
"together, and say,"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kattukāmo assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Venerables, I wish, by means of begging, to build a hut without a "
"sponsoring owner and intended for myself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ kuṭi­vatthu­o­loka­naṃ yācāmī”ti."
msgstr "I request the Order to inspect the site for the hut.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "He should make his request a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid ""
"Sace sabbo saṃgho ussahati kuṭivatthuṃ oloketuṃ, sabbena saṃghena "
"oloketabbaṃ."
msgstr "If the whole Order is able to inspect the site, they should all go."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.255"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid ""
"No ce sabbo saṃgho ussahati kuṭivatthuṃ oloketuṃ, ye tattha honti bhikkhū "
"byattā paṭibalā sārambhaṃ anārambhaṃ saparikkamanaṃ aparikkamanaṃ jānituṃ te "
"yācitvā sammannitabbā."
msgstr ""
"If the whole Order is not able to inspect the site, then those monks there "
"who are competent and capable—who know where harm will be done and where no "
"harm will be done, and who know what is meant by a space on all sides and a "
"lack of space on all sides—should be asked and then appointed."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbā."
msgstr "“And, monks, they should be appointed in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1446"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kattukāmo assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Monk so-and-so, by means of begging, wishes to build a hut without a "
"sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ kuṭi­vatthu­o­loka­naṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to inspect the site for the hut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū "
"sammanneyya itthannāmassa bhikkhuno kuṭivatthuṃ oloketuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should appoint monk so-and-"
"so and monk so-and-so to inspect the site."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.15"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1447"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.16"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.17"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kattukāmo assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Monk so-and-so, by means of begging, wishes to build a hut without a "
"sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.18"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ kuṭi­vatthu­o­loka­naṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to inspect the site for the hut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.19"
msgid ""
"Saṃgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhū sammannati itthannāmassa "
"bhikkhuno kuṭivatthuṃ oloketuṃ."
msgstr ""
"The Order appoints monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to inspect the site."

#. VAR: sammuti → sammati (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.20"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa ca itthannāmassa ca bhikkhūnaṃ sammuti "
"itthannāmassa bhikkhuno kuṭivatthuṃ oloketuṃ, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so to "
"inspect the site for the hut should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.21"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1448"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.22"
msgid ""
"Sammatā saṃghena itthannāmo ca itthannāmo ca bhikkhū itthannāmassa bhikkhuno "
"kuṭivatthuṃ oloketuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Monk so-and-so and monk so-and-so have been appointed by the Order to "
"inspect the site for the hut of monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.23"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.24"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1449"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.25"
msgid ""
"Tehi sammatehi bhikkhūhi tattha gantvā kuṭivatthu oloketabbaṃ, sārambhaṃ "
"anārambhaṃ saparikkamanaṃ aparikkamanaṃ jānitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The appointed monks should go and inspect the site for the hut to find out "
"if any harm will be done and if it has a space on all sides."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.26"
msgid "Sace sārambhaṃ hoti aparikkamanaṃ, “mā idha karī”ti vattabbo."
msgstr ""
"If harm will be done and it lacks a space on all sides, they should say, "
"‘Don’t build here.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.27"
msgid "Sace anārambhaṃ hoti saparikkamanaṃ, saṃghassa ārocetabbaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"If no harm will be done and it has a space on all sides, they should inform "
"the Order:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.28"
msgid "“anārambhaṃ saparikkamanan”ti."
msgstr "‘No harm will be done and it has a space on all sides.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.29"
msgid ""
"Tena kuṭikārakena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ "
"karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ "
"paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr ""
"The monk who wishes to build the hut should then approach the Order, put his "
"robe over one shoulder, pay respect at the feet of the senior monks, squat "
"on his heels with his palms together, and say,"

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.30"
msgid "“ahaṃ, bhante, saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kattukāmo assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, I wish, by means of begging, to build a hut without a "
"sponsoring owner and intended for myself."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.256"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.31"
msgid "Sohaṃ, bhante, saṃghaṃ kuṭi­vatthu­desanaṃ yācāmī”ti."
msgstr "I request the Order to approve the site for the hut.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.32"
msgid "Dutiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "He should make his request a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.33"
msgid "Tatiyampi yācitabbā."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.34"
msgid "“Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should then inform the Order:"

#. </span>
#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1450"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.35"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.36"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kattukāmo assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Monk so-and-so, by means of begging, wishes to build a hut without a "
"sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.37"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ kuṭi­vatthu­desanaṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to approve the site for the hut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.38"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno kuṭivatthuṃ "
"deseyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should approve the site."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.39"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.151"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1451"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.40"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.41"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu saññācikāya kuṭiṃ kattukāmo assāmikaṃ attuddesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Monk so-and-so, by means of begging, wishes to build a hut without a "
"sponsoring owner and intended for himself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.42"
msgid "So saṃghaṃ kuṭi­vatthu­desanaṃ yācati."
msgstr "He is requesting the Order to approve the site for the hut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.43"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno kuṭivatthuṃ deseti."
msgstr "The Order approves the site for the hut of monk so-and-so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.44"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno kuṭivatthussa desanā, so "
"tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of approving the site for the hut should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.45"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1452"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.46"
msgid "Desitaṃ saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno kuṭivatthu."
msgstr "The site for the hut of monk so-and-so has been approved by the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.47"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.2.48"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div></div><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.6.2.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1453"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Sārambhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Where harm will be done:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: undūrānaṃ → undurānaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid ""
"kipillikānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, upacikānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, undūrānaṃ vā āsayo "
"hoti, ahīnaṃ vā āsayo hoti, vicchikānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, satapadīnaṃ vā āsayo "
"hoti, hatthīnaṃ vā āsayo hoti, assānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, sīhānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, "
"byagghānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, dīpīnaṃ vā āsayo hoti, acchānaṃ vā āsayo hoti, "
"taracchānaṃ vā āsayo hoti,"
msgstr ""
"it is the abode of ants, termites, rats, snakes, scorpions, centipedes, "
"elephants, horses, lions, tigers, leopards, bears, or hyenas, or any other "
"animals;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.257"></a>
#. VAR: saṃsa­ra­ṇa­nissitaṃ vā → sañ­cara­ṇa­nissitaṃ vā (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss6:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid ""
"yesaṃ kesañci tiracchā­na­gatā­naṃ pāṇānaṃ āsayo hoti, pubbaṇ­ṇa­nissitaṃ vā "
"hoti, aparaṇ­ṇa­nissitaṃ vā hoti, abbhā­ghāta­nissitaṃ vā hoti, āghāta­na­"
"nissitaṃ vā hoti, susānanissitaṃ vā hoti, uyyānanissitaṃ vā hoti, "
